===Etymology===
Ultimately from {{inh|zh|sit-pro|*ŋa-n||goose}} (tentatively reconstructed); cognate with {{cog|bo|ངང་པ}}, {{cog|my|ငန်း}}.

Related to {{och-l|鵝|domestic goose}}; both {{zh-l|*鵝}} and {{zh-l|*雁}} likely reflect an earlier liquid final ({{zh-ref|Schuessler, 2007}}; cf. Baxter and Sagart's reconstruction). Alternatively, it may derive from {{zh-l|*鵝}} with nominalizing suffix ''*-n'', but this Chinese-internal derivation is problematic in light of the cognates in {{cog|tbq}} ({{zh-ref|Schuessler, 2007}}; {{zh-ref|Alves, 2015b}}); but see {{zh-ref|Hill (2019)}} also, as noted in the etymology of {{zh-l|*鵝}}.

Possible relationship with {{cog|ine-pro|*ǵʰh₂éns||goose}} has been noted by some ({{zh-ref|Mayrhofer, 1976}}; {{zh-ref|Alves, 2015b}}).

